## Proposed Changes

---

### 1. New headless matching adapter

#### [NEW] [matching_adapter.py](file:///c:/Users/DELL%20G3/Desktop/GP/Automation/AI-Automation-New/ai_agent/ai_chat_bot/agents/matching_adapter.py)

A headless (Qt-free) adapter that wraps `universal_pattern_generator.generate_placement_grid()` and converts its grid indices to physical micron coordinates using the geometry engine's `STD_PITCH` and `ROW_PITCH`.

Public function: `apply_matching(nodes, device_ids, technique, pitch, row_pitch) -> (list[dict], MatchedBlock)`

The `MatchedBlock` dataclass carries:
- `block_id`: unique identifier for the matched group
- `member_ids`: set of device IDs in the block
- `anchor_x`, `anchor_y`: block's origin
- `technique`: which matching was applied

After matching, every member node gets tagged with `_matched_block: block_id`. This tag is the key to protecting matched groups from downstream destruction.

